The paper introduces a new type of neural network architecture, MDRNNs, which extends the potential applicability of RNNs to multidimensional domains such as vision, video processing, and medical imaging. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the experimental results of the proposed model, which suggests that it falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
